1> Unless you feel like being a jerk, wait for Garadain to call the charge.  Otherwise, the giants and orcs in front of the fort don't despawn, and it messes the place up for folks who want to hunt there.<br>
<br>
The first few times I was involved in this quest, we just waited for Garadain to walk in the fort.  He doesn't aggro the orcs/giants, and they don't seem to aggro him if they're otherwise engaged with the attacking dwarves. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13>Quests of Norrath</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
